3. English Summary

The Death of Armenias Auto-industry

In the first 10 months of 2023, Armenia witnessed a 3.17-fold increase in car exports compared to the same period in 2022. However, this seemingly positive trend masks the underlying challenges. Georgia, has implemented restrictions on the export of American cars with engines of 1.9 liters and more, as well as hybrid and electric cars, constituting over 90% of Armenias automobile exports. Consequently, after a peak in early 2023, a sharp decline in exports has been recorded. Furthermore, Russia, a significant destination for re-exported cars from Armenia, has tightened regulations on grey imports, impacting the market. As a result, experts predict that in 2024, car importers in Armenia may face substantial losses, potentially leading to a significant drop in car prices in the domestic market. This situation poses a threat to the overall economic landscape, as the auto reexports played a some role in Armenias economic growth in 2022 and 2023.
